tors Probe Pentagon Over Kuwait Strike", "description": "(MENAFN - IANS) Washington, April 28 (IANS) Four senior Democratic senators have launched an investigation into the Pentagon's handling of troop protection during Operation Epic Fury, citing reports ...", "content": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "keywords": null, "creator": null, "language": "english", "country": ["syria", "philippines", "india", "qatar", "malaysia", "bangladesh", "cyprus", "taiwan", "nepal", "israel", "south korea", "yemen", "cambodia", "sri lanka", "indonesia", "kuwait", "georgia", "japan", "lebanon", "bahrain", "armenia", "vietnam", "timor-leste", "jordan", "mongolia", "tajikistan", "brunei", "myanmar", "saudi arabia", "maldives", "united arab emirates", "kyrgyzstan", "china", "north korea", "laos", "iraq", "azerbaijan", "bhutan", "kazakhstan", "thailand", "uzbekistan", "turkey", "singapore", "turkmenistan", "pakistan", "iran", "macau", "afghanistan"], "category": ["top", "politics"], "datatype": "news", "pubDate": "2026-04-27 21:30:53", "pubDateTZ": "UTC", "fetched_at": "2026-04-28 05:05:26", "image_url": "https://menafn.com/updates/pr/2026-04/27/I_41baeimage_story.jpg", "video_url": null, "source_id": "menafn", "source_name": "Menafn", "source_priority": 28392, "source_url": "https://menafn.com", "source_icon": "https://n.bytvi.com/menafn.png", "sentiment": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "sentiment_stats": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_tag": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_region": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_org": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_summary": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "duplicate": true}, {"article_id": "318b019206b74364a4cae5ea2f002bda", "link": "https://saudigazette.com.sa/article/660904/saudi-arabia/tourism-minister-inspects-readiness-of-pilgrims-accommodation-in-makkah", "title": "Tourism minister inspects readiness of pilgrims\u2019 accommodation in Makkah", "description": "MAKKAH \u2014 Minister of Tourism Ahmed Al-Khateeb inspected the readiness of hospitality facilities and temporary accommodations designated for pilgrims during the Hajj season, reviewing the level of services provided to pilgrims at their residences.The tour included hospitality facilities and temporary accommodations across Makkah. He assessed operational procedures, facility preparedness, and the services offered to pilgrims. This contributes to enhancing service quality within accommodation facilities.During the tour, Al-Khateeb met with trained tourism personnel serving pilgrims and reviewed their readiness and role in delivering services. This reflects the impact of the ministry\u2019s training and qualification programs aimed at empowering national talent in the tourism sector.He also visited the Ministry of Tourism branch in Makkah Region. The branch supports the ministry\u2019s year-round field presence, brings services closer to investors and operators, and strengthens monitoring and oversight of hospitality facilities and temporary accommodations designated for pilgrims during the Hajj season.At the Makkah Chamber of Commerce, Al-Khateeb met with investors and operators of hospitality facilities and temporary accommodations. They discussed the sector\u2019s readiness for the Hajj season, explored ways to improve service quality for pilgrims, and enhanced coordination and integration across all aspects of pilgrim accommodation services.He emphasized to investors and operators the importance of providing a hospitality experience that enriches pilgrims' journey to the Grand Mosque. He stressed the need to fulfill the national responsibility of caring for pilgrims, enabling them to perform their rituals in comfort and peace.During the meeting, the minister announced the achievement of the target to increase bed capacity in Makkah\u2019s hospitality sector. He underscored the success of the ministry\u2019s initiatives, including the launch of the \u201cTemporary Accommodation\u201d licensing service for pilgrims and expanded hospitality capacity in Makkah.This year, the Ministry of Tourism assumed full responsibility for overseeing the pilgrim accommodation sector in Makkah. The \u201cTemporary Accommodation\u201d licensing service contributed to adding more than 566,000 beds to the pilgrim hospitality sector in Makkah through a structured framework and clear standards that enhance service quality and diversify accommodation options for pilgrims.", "content": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "keywords": ["hajj season", "hospitality facilities", "makkah", "ahmed al-khateeb", "ministry of tourism", "makkah chamber of commerce", "temporary accommodations"], "creator": ["saudi gazette report"], "language": "english", "country": ["saudi arabia"], "category": ["top", "tourism"], "datatype": "news", "pubDate": "2026-04-27 21:27:14", "pubDateTZ": "UTC", "fetched_at": "2026-04-27 21:41:32", "image_url": "https://saudigazette.com.sa/saudigazette/uploads/images/2026/04/28/2698882.webp", "video_url": null, "source_id": "saudigazette", "source_name": "Saudi Gazette", "source_priority": 356263, "source_url": "https://saudigazette.com.sa", "source_icon": "https://n.bytvi.com/saudigazette.png", "sentiment": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "sentiment_stats": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_tag": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PROFESSIONAL AND CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_region": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_org": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN CORPORATE PLANS", "ai_summary": "ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "duplicate": false}, {"article_id": "af99938c15f92ba32d0e9fc60a070d1d", "link": "https://gulf365.net/iraq-news/13208993/%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%82-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D9%83%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%AA%D8%B4%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%83%D9%88%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%A9.html", "title":